    • Method Detail

      • offer

        public boolean offer(E e,
                     int v)
        Adds an element to the priority queue provided either: (a) the MinHeapPQ doesn't contain another identical element, or (b) the MinHeapPQ does contain an identical element, but the new one has lower priority value. In the latter case, the existing element's priority is decreased, and MinHeapPQ is restructured accordingly.
        Parameters:
        e - The element to add to priority queue
        v - The priority value of e.
        Returns:
        true if the element was added, or false if it was not added due to existing element but with lower priority value.

      • peek

        public E peek()
        Accesses the top of the MinHeapPQ. Does not change the MinHeapPQ
        Returns:
        The element with lowest priority value. Returns null if empty.

      • peekPriority

        public int peekPriority()
        Accesses and returns the priority value of the top of the MinHeapPQ. Does not change the MinHeapPQ.
        Returns:
        The value of the element with lowest priority value. Throws a bounds exception if empty.

      • getPriority

        public int getPriority(E element)
        Gets the priority value of an element that is in the priority queue.
        Parameters:
        element - the element whose priority to get. throws an exception if the element is not in the MinHeapPQ
        Returns:
        the priority of element

      • inPQ

        Returns:
